  "prompt": "What are the best books to learn PHP (Beginner, Advances both)?",
  "response": "Here are some recommended PHP books for different skill levels:\n\nBeginner Level Books:\n1. \"PHP & MySQL: Server-side Web Development\" by Jon Duckett\n- Beginner-friendly\n- Visual and easy to understand\n- Covers fundamentals and practical examples\n\n2. \"PHP for Absolute Beginners\" by Jason Lengstorf\n- Step-by-step approach\n- Clear explanations\n- Great for complete beginners\n\n3. \"Learning PHP, MySQL & JavaScript\" by Robin Nixon\n- Comprehensive introduction\n- Covers multiple web technologies\n- Practical approach\n\nIntermediate Level Books:\n1. \"PHP: The Right Way\" by Josh Lockhart\n- Best practices\n- Modern PHP development\n- Comprehensive guide\n\n2. \"Modern PHP\" by Josh Lockhart\n- Advanced techniques\n- Object-oriented programming\n- Composer, namespaces, and modern practices\n\nAdvanced Level Books:\n1. \"PHP Design Patterns\" by Mario Lurig\n- Advanced design patterns\n- Enterprise-level development\n- Complex architectural concepts\n\n2. \"Clean Code PHP\" by Victor Puertas\n- Code quality and best practices\n- Refactoring techniques\n- Professional development standards\n\nOnline Resources:\n- Official PHP Documentation\n- PHP The Right Way website\n- Laracasts tutorials\n\nBonus: Interactive Learning Platforms:\n- Codecademy\n- Udemy\n- PHP Academy",
